    {
      "id": "overview",
      "title": "Role Overview",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "Mobile interviews assess platform-specific knowledge (iOS/Android), app architecture, performance optimization, and general programming skills. Expect coding challenges, design discussions, and platform deep dives."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**What interviewers assess:**\n\n- Platform expertise (iOS/Swift or Android/Kotlin)\n- Mobile architecture patterns (MVVM, Clean Architecture)\n- UI/UX implementation skills\n- Performance and memory management\n- App lifecycle and background processing"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "format",
      "title": "Common Interview Format",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Typical mobile interview loop:**\n\n1. **Recruiter screen** (30 min)\n2. **Technical phone screen** (45-60 min) - Coding or platform questions\n3. **Onsite/Virtual loop** (4-5 hours):\n   - Platform-specific deep dive\n   - Coding/algorithm round\n   - Mobile system design\n   - Behavioral round"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "content": {
            "text": "Be ready to discuss trade-offs between native and cross-platform approaches. Know when each makes sense."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
